Key Vulnerability ⚠️
Prompt injection via instruction override 🧨
Leakage of system prompt context 🔓
Weak separation between system and user roles 👤⚙️
Mitigation Lessons 🛡️

To secure LLM-based systems:

Never store secrets inside prompts 🔐
Separate system and user contexts strictly ⚙️
Implement backend authorization checks 🧱
Prevent instruction override attacks 🚫
Disable debug / variable exposure in production 🧪
Conclusion 🧾

CupidBot shows how prompt injection attacks can fully compromise AI systems 🤖.
It highlights the importance of proper LLM security design and context isolation 🔐.
